  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Adobe, Mexican Smoked Chili Marinade</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Marinades</cat>
        <cat>Tex-mex</cat>
        <cat>Main dish</cat></categories>
      <yield>4</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>PUNKY SMCD91F</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Oranges -- juice of</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Lime -- juice of</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Chipotle chiles -- (canned)</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Chopped</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3</qty>
          <unit>cloves</unit></amt>
        <item>Garlic -- finely chopped</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Oregano -- crushed</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Cumin seeds</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Black pepper</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Wine vinegar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Salt</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Combine orange and lime juices, chiles garlic, oregano, cumin, black
  pepper, vinegar and salt in blender. Puree until smooth. Makes enough
  marinade for l l/2 to 2 pounds meat or chicken. Do you get the Times. On
  page H 48 there are several marinades which are all low calorie. There is a
  Teriyaki, Tandoori, Berber and Cinnamon-Orange Marinade. If you didn't get
  the paper, do any of these interest you? Please let me know and I'll post
  some for you. P FRISCHKNECHT
  
  Recipe By     :
  
  From: Ladies Home Journal- August 1991
  
